or":{"username":"muon4","cleared":true,"url":"/muon4","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/059/198/429603a5d61e7bc28452e32313e498cdfa655d87_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"localtapiola","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2584556,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::ReportBecamePublic","message":"","markdown_message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-04-10T03:36:59.926Z","updated_at":"2018-04-10T03:36:59.926Z","actor":{"username":"muon4","cleared":true,"url":"/muon4","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/059/198/429603a5d61e7bc28452e32313e498cdfa655d87_original.png/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"localtapiola","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false}],"activity_page_count":1,"activity_page_number":1,"summaries":[{"id":7063,"category":"team","content":"##Issue\nThe reporter found that it was possible to upload svg's and exe's in a reply in a conversation chain and target the receiver of the message .\n\n##Fix\n\nThe possibility to upload files in this specific way was disabled.\n\n##Reasoning\n\nBased on the report, the issue was found to be valid. The report cleary shows how to exploit the vulnerability. Looking into the issue however, showed that this actually quite rarely triggers anything on an updated browser on an updated operating system running updated AV -software. This is very much the case for all Localtapiola workstations. ","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003ch2 id=\"issue\"\u003eIssue\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe reporter found that it was possible to upload svg\u0026#39;s and exe\u0026#39;s in a reply in a conversation chain and target the receiver of the message .\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"fix\"\u003eFix\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe possibility to upload files in this specific way was disabled.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"reasoning\"\u003eReasoning\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBased on the report, the issue was found to be valid. The report cleary shows how to exploit the vulnerability. Looking into the issue however, showed that this actually quite rarely triggers anything on an updated browser on an updated operating system running updated AV -software. This is very much the case for all Localtapiola workstations. \u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"category":"researcher","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false}]}